
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `debconf-updatepo` baraye update kardan file-haye `po` (translate shode) dar package-haye Debian estefade mishavad. In dastoor, translate-haye jadid ra az template file migirad va dar file-haye `po` apply mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--help`  --> ℹ️ Namayesh rahnamaye dastoor
    🔹 `--no-header` --> 🚫 Header-haye default ra dar file `po` ezafe nemikonad.
    🔹 `--create-missing` --> ✨ Agar file `po` vojood nadashte bashad, yek file jadid misazad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ debconf-updatepo -v

    🔹 File-haye `po` ra update mikonad va output-haye bishtar neshon midahad.

    $ debconf-updatepo --create-missing fr

    🔹 File `po` baraye zaban Faransavi ra misazad agar vojood nadashte bashad, va update mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ debconf-updatepo fa

    🔹 File `po` baraye zaban Farsi ra update mikonad. Agar taghirati dar template file bashad, dar file `po` apply mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `debconf-updatepo` command is used to update `po` (translated) files in Debian packages. It fetches new translations from the template file and applies them to the `po` files.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--help`  --> ℹ️ Show command help
    🔹 `--no-header` --> 🚫 Do not add default headers to the `po` file.
    🔹 `--create-missing` --> ✨ Create a new `po` file if it doesn't exist.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ debconf-updatepo -v

    🔹 Updates the `po` files and displays more verbose output.

    $ debconf-updatepo --create-missing fr

    🔹 Creates a `po` file for the French language if it doesn't exist, and updates it.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ debconf-updatepo en

    🔹 Updates the `po` file for the English language. If there are changes in the template file, they are applied to the `po` file.
